630,The-honest--electricity--thief-Experimental-eviden_2025_Journal-of-Behaviora.pdf,"Instead, we use the condonement of electricity theft; it provides 
us with information of how people view this behaviour but does not 
tell us whether they actively engage in it. We are interested whether 
dishonesty levels differ between those that are strictly opposed to 
electricity theft and those that are not. We use stated social norms 
as a tool to analyse behaviour that is not socially desirable. Here, 
we use stated social norms regarding electricity theft as a proxy for 
the individual’s behaviour. We expect that people reporting that most 
people similar to oneself engage in electricity theft are also highly likely 
to engage in electricity theft themselves. We therefore anticipate that 
these people are on average less honest in the game than people who 
report that the minority of people similar to them engages in electricity 
